modules.description: Provides adaptive quadrature algorithms for numerical integration of real-valued functions over intervals. Operates on functions with domain and codomain of type float, supporting both finite and infinite limits. Used to compute definite integrals in scientific computing and mathematical modeling scenarios.

Provides numerical integration using adaptive algorithms, with functions to create workspaces for managing sub-interval limits and to compute integrals with specified absolute and relative accuracy. Operates on integrators, workspaces, and functions that map floats to floats, returning results with error estimates. Used for accurately approximating integrals of functions over intervals, particularly when dealing with complex or oscillatory integrands.
